      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Geneva 5 January 1880 ¶ My dear Baron, ¶  ¶ A letter from me of 6 November 1879 ¶  has crossed with yours of 9 October. ¶  It replied to requests you made about some  ¶ Eucalyptus ¶ . ¶  ¶ On 21 Octob...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="de">80.01.05</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="de">From Alphonse de Candolle</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="de">RB MSS M1, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS annotation in an unknown hand: 'L. linearis being older name' and 'L. nitidulus var leucocaulon = L. linearis.' MS found with a specimen of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Leptorrhynchus linearus</seg> (MEL 248899).</p>
               </note>Genève 5 Janv. 1880</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">Mon cher Baron</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Une letter de moi, du 6 novembre 1879, s'est croisée avec la votre de 9 octobre. Elle répondait à des demandes que vous aviez faites sur des <name key="Eucalyptus">Eucalyptus</name>.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Le 21 octobre vous m'avez écrit au sujet d'un <name key="Leptorhynchus">Leptorhynchus</name> qui vous embarasse. Je l'ai examiné et voici mon opinion, confirmée par celle de Dr Müller, au quel j'ai montré les échantillons.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Votre <name key="Leptorrhynchus%20linearis">Leptorrhynchus linearis</name> Less. (fide Benth.), de Snowy-River, est le L. nitidulus, <seg>β</seg>, leucocaulon DC. Prodr. Il diffère certainement du L. squamatus, du moins des échantillons de Labilliardière. Les squamae sont obtuses, tandis que dans le squamatus elles sont oblongo-acutae. Les feuilles sont moins larges. La variété leucocaulon du nitidulus est peu distincte du vrai nitidulus quant aux feuilles et à l'indument, mais dans notre échantillon unique du nitidulus (Durville) les capitules sont plus avancés que dans la variété, et les squamae (par conséquent?) sont plus larges.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>J'ai à vous remercier du 3ème fascicule de l'Eucalyptographia. Comme je vous l'ai deja dit, peut-être, j'ai parlé de cette publication avec éloge dans les Archives des Sciences physiques et naturelles qui se publie ici.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Nous avons un hiver rigoureux. La plaine de Suisse est couverte de neiges et de brouillards, mais quand on s'elève de quelques centaines de mètres sur les montagnes on jouit d'un beau soleil et au lieu de neige on voit du gazon, même des fleurs. C'est un spectacle magnifique. Les hautes montagnes s'elevent au dessus de la mer des nuages et le ciel est d'une grande pureté.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>En vous adressant tous mes voeux pour l'année actuelle, je suis toujours, mon cher Baron, votre très dévoué</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">Alph. de Candolle</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Geneva 5 January 1880</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">My dear Baron,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>A letter from me of 6 November 1879<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter not found.</p>
               </note> has crossed with yours of 9 October.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M to A. de Candolle, 9 October 1879 (in this edition as 79-10-09a).</p>
               </note> It replied to requests you made about some <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Eucalyptus">Eucalyptus</name>
               </seg>.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to A. de Candolle, 3 September 1879.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>On 21 October you wrote to me on the subject of a <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Leptorhynchus">Leptorhynchus</name>
               </seg>
               <note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     </seg>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Leptorrhynchus</seg>
                     <seg style="">?</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> that perplexes you.<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter not found.</p>
               </note> I have examined it and here is my opinion, confirmed by that of Dr Müller,<note xml:id="ftn7" type="footnote" n="7">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>i.e. Jean Müller.</p>
               </note> to whom I showed the specimens.<note xml:id="ftn8" type="footnote" n="8">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     </seg>M also sought the view of August Eichler in Berlin, see P. Ascherson to M, 3 May 1880. </p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Your <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Leptorrhynchus%20linearis">Leptorrhynchus linearis</name>
               </seg> Less. (fide Benth.<note xml:id="ftn9" type="footnote" n="9">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Bentham (1863-78), vol. 3, p. 611.</p>
               </note>) from the Snowy River is <seg style="font-style: italic; ">L. nitidulus</seg>, <seg>β</seg>, <seg style="font-style: italic; ">leucocaulon</seg> DC Prodr.<note xml:id="ftn10" type="footnote" n="10">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>A. P. de Candolle (1837), p. 160.</p>
               </note> It certainly differs from <seg style="font-style: italic; ">L. squamatus</seg>, at least from Labillardière's specimens. The squamae are obtuse, while in <seg style="font-style: italic; ">squamatus</seg> they are oblong-acute. The leaves are less broad. The <seg style="font-style: italic; ">leucocaulon</seg> variety of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">nitidulus</seg> is little different from the true <seg style="font-style: italic; ">nitidulus</seg> as to the leaves and the indumentum, but in our unique specimen of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">nitidulus</seg> (Durville), the capitula are more advanced than in the variety, and the squamae (as a result?) are broader.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have to thank you for the 3rd fascicle of the <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Eucalyptographia</seg>.<note xml:id="ftn11" type="footnote" n="11">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>B79.13.11, Decade 3.</p>
               </note> As I have perhaps already told you, I have praised this publication in the <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Archives des sciences physiques et naturelles</seg> which is published here.<note xml:id="ftn12" type="footnote" n="12">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>A brief review by Candolle of Decades 1-3 of M's <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Eucalyptographia</seg> appeared in <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Archives des sciences physiques et naturelles</seg>, ser. 3, vol. 3, p. 72, in the issue for January 1880.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>We are having a rigourous winter. The Swiss plain is covered with snow and mist, but when one goes some hundreds of metres up the mountains, one enjoys beautiful sunshine and in place of snow one sees grass, even flowers. It is a magnificent spectacle. The high mountains rise above the sea of clouds and the sky is of great purity.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>With my best wishes for the present year, I remain, dear Baron, yours very truly,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Alph. de Candolle</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Eucalyptus">Eucalyptus</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Leptorhynchus">Leptorhynchus</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Leptorrhynchus%20linearis">Leptorrhynchus linearis</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">Leptorrhynchus nitidulus <seg>β</seg> leucocaulon</p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Leptorrhynchus%20squamatus">Leptorrhynchus squamatus</name>
            </p>
         </div>
      </body>
